I am using rustc version` 1.51.0 (2fd73fabe 2021-03-23)`

Please see the following code snippet and the build errors. It appears that rustc is getting confused trying to resolve method name from a completely unrelated trait and pointing to those in the error logs. This makes error logs unclear and harder to understand:

```
#[test]
    fn trial() {
        struct MyOption<T> {
            item: T,
        }

        impl<U: Copy> MyOption<&U> {
            fn copied(self) -> U {
                *self.item
            }
        }

        let v = vec![1, 2, 3];
        let ov = MyOption { item: &v };
        let ovc = ov.copied();
    }
```

